<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-01-10T13:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-01-10T13:00:00-05:00" n="62" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d62">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">Paris Peace Conf. 763.72/9:
                            Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Commission to Negotiate
                                    Peace</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>
                                </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-01-10T18:00:00+00:00">January 10, 1919—6 p.m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>229. Your 119, January 6th, 9 p.m. Commission agrees with the suggestion
                            that Department make reply to the German proposal along lines adopted by
                            British and French Governments.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Am</hi>[<hi rend="smallcaps">erican</hi>] <hi rend="smallcaps">Mission</hi>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>